{
  "stem": "13623.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Those trips were-- many trips during the day, as many trips as they-- we were on 12 hour shifts.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So as many trips as we could make during the day, we went back and forth, going through that gate, where you go out of the camp, bringing in the barrack into the camp.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Every time we came through that gate back into the camp, there were always two, three, eight-- there were people just dropping.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I-- I surmise now that this was their first taste of the camp working.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "People were not used to this kind of-- of hard labor.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And on top of everything else, they was-- they wouldn't let us drink any water.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "One prisoner couldn't-- went to a-- as we marched by saw a barrel of water.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He ran and he put his face into the water to drink.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The SS just went past after him and just pushed his head into the water until he couldn't breathe anymore.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And just took his hand off and the guy fell down.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He was dead.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He-- he-- I forget the word.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "When you can't breathe anymore--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He suffocated.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As we were building these barracks, whenever a barrack got finished and completed, other prisoners walked-- were moved into it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The-- the Jewish prisoners were living in the barracks while it was being built.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When a barrack was completed, other prisoners moved into it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this pattern repeated itself.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] After a while, they assigned-- we're still the same group, the ones that are still there are still part of the same group that we started out with from our town-- from the camp-- from the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We're still together, most of the same group.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The rabbi of our-- of Stramtura, Hersh Kahan, is with us.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
